,Recommended,245490,15700416,"Posted: 5 May, 2015",all,Y2J1245,"This game is great because it provides a great balance between fun and challenge. The game allows for continuing without getting a Gold or Silver medal, only a Bronze. So if a particular level gets to be too frustrating you can continue on to the next level and then revisit it.The flip side, though, is that once you finish a level and haven't received Gold you feel very compelled to retry, which is great for adding re-playability.I haven't played through completely yet, or any of the DLC but so far I'm enjoying it more than the previous Trials games which I liked as well.There are a few levels that are difficult, mostly because the challenges are unclear. That's about the only time you can blame the game for the frustration it induces. One level in particular is the most searched variant of Trials Fusion, Trials Fusion Big Air. I completed the level with Gold after looking up how others did it for some instructions, but I'm not convinced I could do it again.Odd levels aside I'd definitely recommend it."
